```css
grid-template-columns: <track-size>+ | repeat(<count>, <track-size>) | minmax(<min>, <max>);
```

Defines column sizes in a grid container.

Examples:
```css
grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 2fr;
grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(250px, 1fr));
grid-template-columns: [start] 1fr [center] 2fr [end];
```

Units: `fr` (fraction), `px`, `%`, `em`, `rem`, `auto`, `min-content`, `max-content`, `fit-content()`.

```css
box-sizing: content-box | border-box;
```

- `content-box` (default) — `width`/`height` apply to content only. Padding and border are added on top.
- `border-box` — `width`/`height` include content, padding, and border.

Best practice:
```css
*, *::before, *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

```css
background: <color> <image> <position>/<size> <repeat> <origin> <clip> <attachment>;
```

Shorthand for all background properties. Supports multiple backgrounds separated by commas.

Examples:
```css
background: #f5f5f5;
background: url('img.png') no-repeat center/cover;
background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
```

```css
transition: <property> <duration> <timing-function>? <delay>?;
```

Enables smooth property changes over time.

Examples:
```css
transition: all 0.3s ease;
transition: opacity 200ms, transform 300ms ease-out;
transition: background-color 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
```

Timing functions: `ease`, `linear`, `ease-in`, `ease-out`, `ease-in-out`, `cubic-bezier()`, `steps()`.

Note: Not all properties are animatable (e.g., `display` is not).

```css
animation: <name> <duration> <timing-function>? <delay>? <count>? <direction>? <fill-mode>? <play-state>?;
```

Examples:
```css
animation: fadeIn 0.3s ease-in-out;
animation: slide 1s ease infinite alternate;
animation: pulse 2s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.6, 1) infinite;
```

`fill-mode`: `none`, `forwards` (retain end state), `backwards` (apply start state during delay), `both`.
`direction`: `normal`, `reverse`, `alternate`, `alternate-reverse`.

```css
transform: <transform-function>+;
```

2D functions: `translate(x, y)`, `rotate(angle)`, `scale(x, y)`, `skew(x, y)`, `matrix()`.
3D functions: `translate3d()`, `rotate3d()`, `scale3d()`, `perspective()`.

Examples:
```css
transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(-50%);
transform: rotate(45deg) scale(1.2);
transform: perspective(500px) rotateY(30deg);
```

Multiple transforms are applied right-to-left. Creates a new stacking context.

```css
var(--custom-property, fallback-value)
```

Accesses CSS custom properties (CSS variables).

Defined with `--` prefix:
```css
:root {
  --primary: #3490dc;
  --spacing: 1rem;
}
.btn {
  color: var(--primary);
  padding: var(--spacing, 0.5rem);
}
```

Custom properties are inherited. Fallback is used when the property is undefined. Fallbacks can be nested: `var(--a, var(--b, #000))`.

```css
@keyframes <name> {
  from { /* 0% */ }
  <percentage> { /* intermediate */ }
  to { /* 100% */ }
}
```

Defines animation keyframes. Referenced by `animation-name`.

Example:
```css
@keyframes slideIn {
  0% { transform: translateX(-100%); opacity: 0; }
  100% { transform: translateX(0); opacity: 1; }
}
```

Multiple keyframes can share percentages: `0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }`.

```css
container-type: normal | size | inline-size;
```

Establishes an element as a containment context for container queries.

- `normal` — no containment (default)
- `inline-size` — containment on the inline axis only
- `size` — containment on both axes

Used with `@container` queries:
```css
.card { container-type: inline-size; }
@container (min-width: 400px) {
  .card-body { display: flex; }
}
```
